        <trans-unit id="160" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Example 2: Interest by range = Days</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="161" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You set up an interest code that assesses interest one time for every 15 days that the invoice payment exceeds the transaction due date.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="162" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You want to base the calculation on an amount interest value, according to stepped day intervals.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="163" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The interest value will be 10.00 per 15 days during the first 60 days, 15.00 per 15 days during days 61 to 90, and 20.00 per 15 days from day 91 and after.</source>
        </trans-unit>
