        <trans-unit id="185" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You set up an interest code that assesses interest one time for every month that the invoice payment exceeds the transaction due date.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="186" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You want to base the calculation on a percentage interest value, according to stepped month intervals.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="187" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The interest value will be 1.5 percent per month for the first three overdue months, 2.0 percent per month for the second three months, and 2.5 percent per month for each month beyond the first six months.</source>
        </trans-unit>
